# üêû bug report

### Affected Package

@angular/upgrade


### Is this a regression?

No


### Description

When extending UpgradeComponent, it creates a new scope for the upgraded component. In my case, I need to be able to access this scope to ensure any other controllers or components I create are created using this new scope. 


## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction

export class ExtensionClass extends UpgradeComponent {
  constructor(elementRef: ElementRef, injector: Injector) {
    super(COMPONENT_NAME, elementRef, injector);

    // Currently, we can't access this component scope because its private. If it was a protected field this line would work.
    this.scope = this.$componentScope;
  }
}

